Stenoma coniophaea is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1930. It is found in Par√°, Brazil.The wingspan is about 28 mm. The forewings are light grey sprinkled fuscous, with the extreme costal edge white except towards the apex. The plical and second discal stigmata are very obscure and grey. There is a marginal series of dark grey dots around the apex and termen. The hindwings are grey whitish, the apical edge slightly suffused grey.